The paper proposes a semi-supervised approach for network traffic classification using machine learning algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
